{
  "doc_id": "26222",
  "text": "There is some evidence that HA can both mediate and modulate BMP7 responses. In chondrocytes, BMP7-dependent Smad1 signaling was mediated through CD44-Smad1 interactions [CITATION_1] . Other studies demonstrated that pericellular HA augments BMP7 Smad signaling [CITATION_2] . In renal epithelial cells, BMP7 has also been shown to induce the formation of HA cables [CITATION_3] . However, whether HA plays a specific role in BMP7-mediated antagonism of TGF-␤1 actions is not known. In this work, we demonstrate a novel mechanism in which BMP7 reverses TGF-␤1 induction of myofibroblast differentiation in human lung fibroblast cultures by internalizing pericellular HA into catalytic endosomes within the cytoplasm and preventing TGF-␤1-driven pericellular HA accumulation. The CD44 variant isoform, CD44v7/8, and membrane-bound Hyal2 are both critical for this process of HA internalization and thus potentially present new targets for study and intervention in fibrosis.",
